Package com.bluegosling.collections.maps

New interfaces and implementations related to the standard Java Map interface.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    MapBuilder<K,V,M extends Map<K,V>,B extends MapBuilder<K,V,M,B>>
    An interface for imperatively constructing a map using a builder pattern and method chaining.
    RandomAccessNavigableMap<K,V>
    A navigable map that provides random access over its elements.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractRandomAccessNavigableMap<K,V>
    An abstract base class for RandomAccessNavigableMap implementations.
    AbstractRandomAccessNavigableMap.SubMapByIndicesIterator<K,V>
    Implements an iterator over a sub-map (by indices) of elements for the various set views of this map.
    DescendingRandomAccessMap<K,V>  
    HamtMap<K,V>
    An implementation of Map that uses a hash array-mapped trie (HAMT).
    LinearHashingMap<K,V>  
    SortedArrayMap<K,V>  
    WeightBalancedTreeMap<K,V>
    A binary search tree that always maintains perfect balance.
